def checkPossibility(nums):
    cnt = 0
    for i in range(1, len(nums)):
        if nums[i] < nums[i - 1]:
            cnt += 1
            if i == 1 or nums[i] >= nums[i - 2]:
                nums[i-1] = nums[i]
            else:
                nums[i] = nums[i - 1]
            if cnt > 1:
                return False
    return True
```

    We iterate through the given array and, if we find a decreasing pair, we increment a counter `cnt`. We then modify either the current element or the previous element to make the array non-decreasing, choosing the optimal modification based on a comparison with the element two positions before. If we find more than one decreasing pair, we return false, as it implies that we need to modify more than one element to make the array non-decreasing. If we reach the end of the iteration, we return true, as the array could be made non-decreasing by modifying at most one element.

